After five incredible years of ownership, it's with a heavy heart that I have to say goodbye to my C4S. This car has been more than just a mode of transportation; it's been a part of my life, my memories, my adventures.

Here are photos I’ve never shared for one last time 🥹

I remember the thrill of driving it for the first time, the rush of adrenaline as I revved the engine and hit the gas. I remember the countless road trips and weekend getaways, the stunning landscapes and scenic routes that I've had the pleasure of experiencing from behind the wheel of this amazing machine.

But as much as it pains me to let it go, it's time for me to move on and make room for new adventures. I'll always cherish the memories I've made with this car.

Not to worry, it’s going to a great home to a nice couple in Jaskson Hole Wyoming where an all-wheel drive Porsche will feel at home. They promise to keep me up-to-date with more beautiful pictures to share. Thanks for following my adventures in Porsche photography! 🥹
